    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Adventurer's Armory 2 pg. 16</em><br/><strong>Price</strong> <img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\"/> 200 gp (expanded), <img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\"/> 50 gp (standard); <strong>Weight</strong> 5 lbs. (expanded), 3 lbs. (standard)</p><h2 class=\"framing\">Description</h2><p>This leather-bound reference tome contains several alphabets used in the various languages of Golarion, along with extensively cross-referenced and indexed words, phrases, and idioms. As long as you speak at least three languages, consulting a standard linguist's codex grants you a +2 circumstance bonus on Linguistics checks when communicating in a language you do not speak.<br/><br/> An expanded linguist's codex has far more phrases and guidance, including instructions to pronounce the sounds in a correct and pleasing manner. These codices provide a +2 circumstance bonus on Diplomacy checks when communicating in a language you do not speak.</p>",
